 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Forest Cover Type Classification\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 22 of 100** — Predict forest cover type from cartographic variables.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"EDA -> preprocessing -> baseline -> LazyPredict -> FLAML -> top-3 evaluation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Predict which of **7 forest cover types** a 30x30m cell belongs to, using 54 cartographic features (elevation, aspect, slope, soil type, wilderness area). The dataset has 581,012 rows — we cap to 50,000 for efficient training. This is a **medium-hard** multiclass problem.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Large-scale 7-class classification\\n\", \"2. Mixed numeric + binary features (one-hot soil/wilderness already encoded)\\n\", \"3. Row sampling for large datasets\\n\", \"4. Macro-F1 and accuracy evaluation\\n\", \"5. LazyPredict and FLAML benchmarking\\n\", \"6. Understanding cartographic feature importance\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Given 54 cartographic features, predict the forest cover type (1-7).\\n\", \"\\n\", \"7-class classification. Macro-F1 is the primary metric.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Forestry managers | Land management planning |\\n\", \"| Ecologists | Habitat mapping |\\n\", \"| Remote sensing | Automated land classification |\\n\", \"| ML learners | Large multiclass with mixed features |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Source | UCI / Kaggle |\\n\", \"| Kaggle slug | uciml/forest-cover-type-dataset |\\n\", \"| Rows | 581,012 (sampled to 50,000) |\\n\", \"| Features | 54 (10 numeric + 44 binary) |\\n\", \"| Target | Cover_Type (1-7) |\\n\", \"| Class balance | Imbalanced — types 1,2 dominate |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- UCI ML Repository / Kaggle: uciml/forest-cover-type-dataset\\n\", \"- License: CC0 Public Domain.\\n\", \"- Roosevelt National Forest, northern Colorado.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\",\\\"flaml\\\",\\\"kagglehub\\\",\\\"xgboost\\\",\\\"lightgbm\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, f1_score, ConfusionMatrixDisplay, classification_report)\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\"); sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\"); SEED=42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"uciml/forest-cover-type-dataset\\\"\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"Cover_Type\\\"\\n\", \"MAX_ROWS = 50000\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.15; VAL_SIZE = 0.15; SEED = 42; FLAML_BUDGET = 120\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Target: {TARGET}, Max rows: {MAX_ROWS}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    raise RuntimeError(f\\\"Download failed: {e}\\\")\\n\", \"csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path,\\\"**\\\",\\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Raw shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"if len(df_raw) > MAX_ROWS:\\n\", \"    df_raw = df_raw.sample(MAX_ROWS, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Sampled to: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df_raw.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"if \\\"Id\\\" in df.columns: df = df.drop(columns=[\\\"Id\\\"])\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Duplicates: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"assert TARGET in df.columns\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTarget:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts().sort_index()}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,4))\\n\", \"df[TARGET].value_counts().sort_index().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=sns.color_palette(\\\"Set2\\\", 7))\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Forest Cover Type Distribution\\\"); ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Cover Type\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"num_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c != TARGET and df[c].nunique() > 2]\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15,8))\\n\", \"for ax, col in zip(axes.flat, num_cols[:6]):\\n\", \"    df.boxplot(column=col, by=TARGET, ax=ax)\\n\", \"    ax.set_title(col); ax.set_xlabel(\\\"\\\")\\n\", \"plt.suptitle(\\\"Numeric Features by Cover Type\\\", y=1.01)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(\\\"Numeric feature stats:\\\")\\n\", \"print(df[num_cols].describe().T[[\\\"mean\\\",\\\"std\\\",\\\"min\\\",\\\"max\\\"]])\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"7 cover types, imbalanced. Types 1 and 2 dominate; types 4 and 6 are rare.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(df[TARGET].value_counts(normalize=True).sort_index())\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET]); y = df[TARGET]\\n\", \"X_tmp, X_test, y_tmp, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y)\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_tmp, y_tmp, test_size=VAL_SIZE/(1-TEST_SIZE), random_state=SEED, stratify=y_tmp)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"10 numeric features get StandardScaler. 44 binary (soil/wilderness) pass through.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"num_cols = [c for c in X_train.columns if X_train[c].nunique() > 2]\\n\", \"bin_cols = [c for c in X_train.columns if X_train[c].nunique() <= 2]\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\\n\", \"    (\\\"num\\\", StandardScaler(), num_cols),\\n\", \"    (\\\"bin\\\", \\\"passthrough\\\", bin_cols)\\n\", \"])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Numeric: {len(num_cols)}, Binary: {len(bin_cols)}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- ELEVATION_SLOPE: elevation * slope interaction\\n\", \"- TOTAL_HYDRO_DIST: sum of horizontal + vertical distance to hydrology\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def eng(d):\\n\", \"    d = d.copy()\\n\", \"    if \\\"Elevation\\\" in d.columns and \\\"Slope\\\" in d.columns:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"ELEV_SLOPE\\\"] = d[\\\"Elevation\\\"] * d[\\\"Slope\\\"]\\n\", \"    hd = [c for c in d.columns if \\\"Hydrology\\\" in c or \\\"hydrology\\\" in c.lower()]\\n\", \"    if len(hd) >= 2:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"TOTAL_HYDRO\\\"] = d[hd[0]].abs() + d[hd[1]].abs()\\n\", \"    return d\\n\", \"X_train=eng(X_train); X_val=eng(X_val); X_test=eng(X_test)\\n\", \"num_cols = [c for c in X_train.columns if X_train[c].nunique() > 2]\\n\", \"bin_cols = [c for c in X_train.columns if X_train[c].nunique() <= 2]\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\\n\", \"    (\\\"num\\\", StandardScaler(), num_cols),\\n\", \"    (\\\"bin\\\", \\\"passthrough\\\", bin_cols)\\n\", \"])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Features: {X_train.shape[1]}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"for name, clf in [(\\\"Dummy\\\",DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\",random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"LogReg\\\",LogisticRegression(max_iter=500,random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"RF\\\",RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1))]:\\n\", \"    pipe = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\",preprocessor),(\\\"clf\\\",clf)])\\n\", \"    pipe.fit(X_train, y_train); yp=pipe.predict(X_val)\\n\", \"    r={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp),\\\"Macro-F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\")}\\n\", \"    results[name]=r; print(f\\\"{name}: {r}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_val_lp=preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"lazy=LazyClassifier(verbose=0,ignore_warnings=True,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp,_=lazy.fit(X_train_lp,X_val_lp,y_train,y_val)\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl=AutoML()\\n\", \"automl.fit(X_train_lp,y_train,task=\\\"classification\\\",metric=\\\"macro_f1\\\",time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,seed=SEED,verbose=0)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"yp_fl=automl.predict(X_val_lp)\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp_fl),\\\"Macro-F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp_fl,average=\\\"macro\\\")}\\n\", \"print(results[\\\"FLAML\\\"])\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier; has_lgbm=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_lgbm=False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier; has_xgb=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_xgb=False\\n\", \"top3={}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm: top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"]=LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=500,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=8,random_state=SEED,verbose=-1,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"]=ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=500,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"if has_xgb: top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"]=XGBClassifier(n_estimators=500,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=8,random_state=SEED,verbosity=0,n_jobs=-1,eval_metric=\\\"mlogloss\\\")\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"]=AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=300,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"top3[\\\"GradBoosting\\\"]=GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=300,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=6,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_tr_t=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_te_t=preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"labels=[f\\\"Type {i}\\\" for i in sorted(y.unique())]\\n\", \"final={}\\n\", \"for name,mdl in top3.items():\\n\", \"    mdl.fit(X_tr_t,y_train); yp=mdl.predict(X_te_t)\\n\", \"    final[name]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_test,yp),\\\"Macro-F1\\\":f1_score(y_test,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\")}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\"); print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=labels))\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(final).T\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,len(top3),figsize=(6*len(top3),5))\\n\", \"if len(top3)==1: axes=[axes]\\n\", \"for ax,(n,m) in zip(axes,top3.items()):\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test,m.predict(X_te_t),ax=ax,cmap=\\\"Blues\\\"); ax.set_title(n)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"bm=list(top3.values())[0]; ypb=bm.predict(X_te_t)\\n\", \"misclass = (y_test.values != ypb).sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Misclassified: {misclass}/{len(y_test)} ({misclass/len(y_test):.1%})\\\")\\n\", \"# Most confused pairs\\n\", \"from collections import Counter\\n\", \"confused = Counter(zip(y_test.values[y_test.values!=ypb], ypb[y_test.values!=ypb]))\\n\", \"print(\\\"\\\\nMost confused pairs (true, pred):\\\")\\n\", \"for pair, cnt in confused.most_common(5):\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"  {pair}: {cnt}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Elevation is the strongest predictor. Cover types 1 and 2 are most common. Types 4 and 6 are hardest to classify due to rarity.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 25. Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Single region (Roosevelt NF, Colorado)\\n\", \"2. 30x30m resolution loses fine detail\\n\", \"3. No temporal dimension\\n\", \"4. Sampled from 581k rows\\n\", \"5. Pre-encoded binary features\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 26. How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Use full 581k rows with LightGBM\\n\", \"2. Feature selection / PCA on soil types\\n\", \"3. Cross-validation\\n\", \"4. Class-weighted models\\n\", \"5. Spatial analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 27. Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Region-specific model — retrain for other forests\\n\", \"- Integrate with GIS systems\\n\", \"- Satellite imagery could complement\\n\", \"- Annual retraining as forests change\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 28. Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Not handling the 44 binary columns properly\\n\", \"2. Not sampling large datasets\\n\", \"3. Using accuracy alone (imbalanced)\\n\", \"4. Ignoring rare cover types\\n\", \"5. Not using stratified splits\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 29. Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Use only elevation — accuracy?\\n\", \"2. PCA on 44 binary features\\n\", \"3. Merge rare classes — does it help?\\n\", \"4. Feature importance ranking\\n\", \"5. Which pairs are most confused?\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
